Introduction

Park Hyung-sik, known mononymously as Hyungsik, is a South Korean singer and actor. He made his official debut on January 7, 2010 as a member of the boy group ZE:A and its sub-group ZE:A Five.

As an actor, he is known for his roles in The Heirs (2013), Hwarang: The Poet Warrior Youth (2016), Strong Girl Bong-soon (2017), Happiness (2021), Soundtrack #1 (2022) and Doctor Slump (2024).
